    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-09T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="266"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1085.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-09T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 7th, 12 noon. Department will at once endeavor to arrange advance if
                    you are sure that the payment of $500,000 on back salaries will enable the
                    Government to continue and enact the reforms suggested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
